        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 18 at 8:15PM PDT by NWS San Diego CA</headline>
        <description>At 815 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Indio, moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Indio, Coachella, Palm Desert, Thermal, La Quinta, Indian Wells,
Thousand Palms, Bermuda Dunes, Sky Valley, and Santa Rosa Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
